  "body": "On Snap Sync currently we have two important type of logs:\n1. `SNAP - progress of State Ranges (Phase 1): 99.21875% [********* ]`\n2. `State Sync 00.03:57:18 | ~0.34 % | 348.79MB / ~101760.00MB | branches: 83.59 % | kB/s: 532 | accounts 119343 | nodes 1215576 | diagnostics: 17.240.43ms`\n\nUsers often are afraid, that after Phase 1, when percentage drops to 0 on state sync, process is restarted when in reality Phase 2 started. \nIt would be great to rework those 2 logs to something like this:\n1. `SNAP - progress of State Ranges (Phase 1 of 2): 99.21875% [********* ]`\n2. `State Sync (Phase 2 of 2) 00.03:57:18 | ~0.34 % | 348.79MB / ~101760.00MB | branches: 83.59 % | kB/s: 532 | accounts 119343 | nodes 1215576 | diagnostics: 17.240.43ms`\n\nAdditionally we need to adjust percentage progress on state sync since it is worrying for a users that it is progressing so slowly when in reality it can end after 30 minutes in 1% of progress.",
